line_1: Hid in the Slime the Toad of Form uncouth
line_2: (That Fish is all one vast extended Mouth)

line_1: Deep-rooted Mould, and Ergot's horn uncouth,
line_2: And break the Canker's desolating tooth.

line_1: Their liberty requir'd no rites uncouth,
line_2: Her rule was gentle and her voice was truth,

line_1: Make poorer still by jargon most uncouth;
line_2: With ev'ry pert, prim Prettiness of Youth

line_1: MY size is large, my shape's uncouth,
line_2: Mens hands have form'd my skin so smooth:
